    <note>Li(2) Zhongxin [19674] CBD has him as the father of the wrong Li Mu. He was learned and especially expert on the Li and Shi, but was juren twice and failed the metropolitan exam twice. The family was a distinguished lineage of Yanzhou since they moved there seven generations earlier. He was a large landowner, philanthropist, and probably a patron of scholarship. Jinshi xubian, 15.39a-41b. CBD, 2, 918-9, 994-5.</note>
